        <name>35.4.4.4 Independent vs. mutually exclusive events</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;h4 class="HELM_exercise"&gt; Exercise &lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt; If \(A\) and \(B\) are two events associated with an experiment and \(\displaystyle{\mathbb{P}(A) = {@pa@}}\), \(\displaystyle{\mathbb{P}(A\cup B) = {@pab@}}\) and \(\displaystyle{\mathbb{P}(B) = p}\), find:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
&lt;li&gt; the choice of \(p\) for which \(A\) and \(B\) are mutually exclusive; &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; the choice of \(p\) for which \(A\) and \(B\) are independent. &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt; Give these probabilities as fractions, rather than decimals: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
&lt;li&gt; For mutually exclusive events \(A\) and \(B\), we have \(p=\quad\)[[input:ans1]][[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]] &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; For independent events \(A\) and \(B\), we have \(p=\quad\)[[input:ans2]][[validation:ans2]][[feedback:prt2]] &lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;h4 class="HELM_solution"&gt; Solution &lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt; For events \(A\) and \(B\) we have\[\mathbb{P}(A\cup B) = \mathbb{P}(A) + \mathbb{P}(B) - \mathbb{P}(A\cap B). \]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
&lt;li&gt; If \(A\) and \(B\) are mutually exclusive then \(\mathbb{P}(A\cap B) = 0\) and therefore\[\mathbb{P}(A\cup B) = \mathbb{P}(A) + \mathbb{P}(B) \]which rearranges to give \(p = \displaystyle {@ta1@}.\)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; If \(A\) and \(B\) are independent then \(\mathbb{P}(A\cap B) = \mathbb{P}(A)\mathbb{P}(B)\) so that\[\mathbb{P}(A\cup B) = \mathbb{P}(A) + \mathbb{P}(B) - \mathbb{P}(A)\mathbb{P}(B)\]which rearranges to give \(p =\displaystyle&amp;nbsp; {@ta2@}.\)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</generalfeedback>
